@node "deadalus" "The Deadalus Encounter"

 Daedalus Encounter: It runs on any machine, but the faster the better
 for  some of the arcade sequences. Later in the game, you almost need
 a Warp Engine or a CyberStorm to get past one challenge, since slower
 machines  don't  update  the display fast enough. Still, in 256 color
 mode it is playable on a stock '040 (25 mhz). Much  beter  in  15-bit
 color mode though!

Daedalus Encounter:  Full-Motion Video Adventure; 3 CD Roms.  Over 2 hours
of live-action video.  You and 2 crew mates have crashed your ship into a
large object which is hurtling towards the sun.  The three of you must work
together to stay alive.  Most of the video scenes are not interactive; they
serve to tell the story.  There are some interactive action sequences, but
most of the gameplay revolves around geometric puzzles.  Often you will
need to solve a puzzle to open a door, turn on equipment, etc.  You can
save your game at any time, and multiple saves are strongly recomended.
Published by Virgin.

Tested on: A4000 with Macro-System's WARP ENGINE '040 running at 40 Mhz
Cybervision-64 (4-meg)
Toshiba 6.7 speed SCSI-II CD-ROM
Amiga OS 3.1

<Tested by: adburns@awod.com - (Adam Burns)>

@endnode


