@node "dragonslair" "Dragon's Lair"

Dragon's Lair
Very fast at 320x240 12 fps
At 640x480 is slow (6 fps)
tested on A4000/040 36MHz 20MB RAM, Picasso II/CGfx

----------

Dragon's Lair:  Cartoon Video Adventure Game.  Control the actions of Dirk
the Daring as you try to rescue the fair princess from the clutches of an
evil dragon.  100% port of the classic laser-disk game found in arcades in
the middle 1980's.  Gameplay consists of moving the joystick or hitting the
fire button at the proper moment to keep the video playing.  Entirely a
game of rote memorization and trial & error.  Still, if you liked the
arcade version, this is a must-have!  Published by ReadySoft.

Tested on: A4000 with Macro-System's WARP ENGINE '040 running at 40 Mhz
Cybervision-64 (4-meg)
Toshiba 6.7 speed SCSI-II CD-ROM
Amiga OS 3.1

<Tested by: adburns@awod.com - (Adam Burns)>

@endnode


